<item>
            <title>[LU-629] _debug_req() never prints out opcode/flags/status</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-629</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The 2.x _debug_req() function was changed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=16359&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=16359&lt;/a&gt; (commit 5467a860213d454759bdfad91503691d6692b317) to avoid problems with accessing unswabbed message buffers.  Unfortunately, this broke the printing of many useful _debug_req() messages, because it didn&apos;t check whether swabbing was actually needed in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, in ptlrpc_expire_one_request() some extra debugging information was added in commit 368689640e6a42a152eee73d354dd6f68836065b, but never removed, making this common message overly verbose.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="11560">LU-629</key>
            <summary>_debug_req() never prints out opcode/flags/status</summary>
